The Abilene Taylor County Public Health District reports the first COVID-19 related death for Taylor County on Saturday April 4 2020. The patient confirmed with COVID-19 passed away in Hendrick Medical Center. “The deceased patient was a female in her 40s and a resident of Disability Resources Inc. (DRI) with underlying medical conditions. The patient was taken to an area hospital after developing symptoms of COVID-19 and having direct contact with a previously identified COVID-19 positive DRI resident. She later tested positive for COVID-19 and was hospitalized until the time of her death.”
